 :tx/rationale "DEEP-REVIEW-1: Root cause of 4 failing guidance tests identified. The C8-FIX-5 code path in telemetry_from_store() (methodology.rs:404-425) checks for :spec/element-type datoms to distinguish 'braid-like projects' from 'external projects'. The 4 failing tests create :spec/inv-test-XXX entities with :db/ident but do NOT create :spec/element-type datoms. So store_has_spec_datoms = false, triggering the external-project fallback which gives spec_language credit only when :exploration/body or :task/title datoms exist. The tests only have :db/doc datoms, so total_spec = 0 instead of the expected 5 or 3. The fix has two parts: (1) Update the tests to include :spec/element-type datoms for entities that represent spec elements — this makes the tests accurately model a spec-using project. (2) Consider whether the C8-FIX-5 detection should ALSO check for :db/ident starting with ':spec/' as a secondary indicator of a spec-aware project, since that's the pattern actually used by spec entities. This is important: the test failures are NOT a regression in M(t) logic — they are a test/code divergence caused by the C8-FIX-5 enhancement that properly handles external projects but left the tests behind."
